{"article_id":"AtsgsKFw7MPvvisk","edus":[{"id":0,"text":"President Donald Trump says","depth":6},{"id":1,"text":"he ' s finally going to do what he ' s long threatened :","depth":7},{"id":2,"text":"tear up NAFTA .","depth":7},{"id":3,"text":"Trump ' s warning came","depth":7},{"id":4,"text":"as he left the G20 meeting in Buenos Aires , Argentina , this weekend .","depth":7},{"id":5,"text":"There , Trump , along with former Mexican President Enrique Peña Nieto and Canadian Prime Minister Justin Trudeau , signed the replacement for NAFTA","depth":7},{"id":6,"text":"- called the United States-Mexico-Canada-Agreement , or USMCA ,","depth":8},{"id":7,"text":"as Trump has rebranded it stateside .","depth":8},{"id":8,"text":"\" I ' ll be terminating it within a relatively short period of time , \"","depth":6},{"id":9,"text":"Trump said Saturday of the original NAFTA .","depth":6},{"id":10,"text":"\" We get rid of NAFTA .","depth":6},{"id":11,"text":"It ' s been a disaster for the United States . \"","depth":6},{"id":12,"text":"Trump ' s threat is intended for Congress","depth":6},{"id":13,"text":"- especially Democrats ,","depth":7},{"id":14,"text":"who have objected to elements of the renegotiated trilateral trade pact with Mexico and Canada .","depth":7},{"id":15,"text":"The House of Representatives and the Senate must approve the USMCA ,","depth":7},{"id":16,"text":"and both parties have voiced reservations .","depth":7},{"id":17,"text":"Democrats don ' t think","depth":8},{"id":18,"text":"it does enough","depth":9},{"id":19,"text":"to protect American jobs and workers ,","depth":9},{"id":20,"text":"and some Republicans see the new deal as too protectionist .","depth":7},{"id":21,"text":"The withdrawal threat is a Trumpian ultimatum :","depth":7},{"id":22,"text":"Take my trade deal ,","depth":8},{"id":23,"text":"or there ' s no deal at all .","depth":8},{"id":24,"text":"Trump loathes NAFTA .","depth":9},{"id":25,"text":"He has called it the \" worst trade deal","depth":10},{"id":26,"text":"ever signed. \"","depth":10},{"id":27,"text":"He has threatened to tear up the trade pact in the past ,","depth":9},{"id":28,"text":"but was ultimately persuaded to renegotiate the agreement ,","depth":10},{"id":29,"text":"leading to the USMCA .","depth":10},{"id":30,"text":"Trump has touted the USMCA as a historic trade deal ,","depth":8},{"id":31,"text":"even though it ' s really an updated and revised version of NAFTA","depth":9},{"id":32,"text":"- which itself is a nearly 25-year-old agreement","depth":10},{"id":33,"text":"negotiated by George H.W . Bush .","depth":10},{"id":34,"text":"So Trump got a new deal","depth":7},{"id":35,"text":"and declared victory .","depth":7},{"id":36,"text":"And now he ' s wielding NAFTA as a political cudgel .","depth":6},{"id":37,"text":"The president ' s threat is serious ,","depth":5},{"id":38,"text":"but it faces a few potential pitfalls .","depth":5},{"id":39,"text":"Trump can likely unilaterally pull out of NAFTA ,","depth":5},{"id":40,"text":"but Congress has a lot more power on trade than on other international agreements ,","depth":7},{"id":41,"text":"and experts say","depth":8},{"id":42,"text":"lawmakers could find ways","depth":9},{"id":43,"text":"to protect NAFTA","depth":10},{"id":44,"text":"or limit Trump on trade in other ways .","depth":10},{"id":45,"text":"Even if Trump invokes Article 2205 of NAFTA","depth":10},{"id":46,"text":"- the mechanism","depth":11},{"id":47,"text":"a country can use","depth":12},{"id":48,"text":"to leave the pact -","depth":12},{"id":49,"text":"the process is not immediate :","depth":9},{"id":50,"text":"It requires a six-month of withdrawal ,","depth":10},{"id":51,"text":"after which Trump can decide to leave .","depth":10},{"id":52,"text":"That six-month timeline matters .","depth":9},{"id":53,"text":"Congress could certainly take up and vote on USMCA before then , in 2019 .","depth":8},{"id":54,"text":"US Trade Representative Robert Lighthizer , the administration ' s chief trade negotiator , told reporters last week","depth":9},{"id":55,"text":"he wants the USMCA to pass with strong bipartisan support ,","depth":10},{"id":56,"text":"which might not happen","depth":11},{"id":57,"text":"if the administration tries to strong-arm Congress .","depth":11},{"id":58,"text":"The administration has threatened NAFTA withdrawal before","depth":7},{"id":59,"text":"to pressure Congress , most notably in the spring of this year .","depth":7},{"id":60,"text":"It never pulled the trigger , though ,","depth":6},{"id":61,"text":"and there are good reasons why .","depth":6},{"id":62,"text":"Congress does have a degree of leverage ,","depth":8},{"id":63,"text":"and","depth":9},{"id":64,"text":"even if Trump succeeds ,","depth":10},{"id":65,"text":"ripping apart the original NAFTA would generate incredible economic uncertainty ,","depth":11},{"id":66,"text":"potentially dealing a tremendous blow to business and manufacturing","depth":12},{"id":67,"text":"and putting jobs at risk .","depth":12},{"id":68,"text":"Trump could blame Congress","depth":10},{"id":69,"text":"all he wants ,","depth":10},{"id":70,"text":"but the chaos would lead back to him .","depth":9},{"id":71,"text":"Trump might not risk it in the end .","depth":8},{"id":72,"text":"Then again , in trade as in everything else , Trump has embraced unorthodox","depth":7},{"id":73,"text":"- and rarely predicable -","depth":7},{"id":74,"text":"tactics .","depth":6},{"id":75,"text":"Trump can likely unilaterally pull out of NAFTA","depth":7},{"id":76,"text":"by invoking Article 2205 ,","depth":8},{"id":77,"text":"which gives Canada and Mexico a six-month notice of the president ' s intent","depth":9},{"id":78,"text":"to terminate the agreement .","depth":9},{"id":79,"text":"This doesn ' t end NAFTA outright","depth":8},{"id":80,"text":"( Mexico and Canada can still stay in ) ,","depth":8},{"id":81,"text":"and , in theory , Trump could change his mind in the six-month time window .","depth":8},{"id":82,"text":"But after that it all becomes murky .","depth":8},{"id":83,"text":"Experts say","depth":7},{"id":84,"text":"that Congress likely has some ability","depth":9},{"id":85,"text":"to protect NAFTA ,","depth":9},{"id":86,"text":"or can use its powers","depth":9},{"id":87,"text":"to curtail Trump on trade elsewhere .","depth":9},{"id":88,"text":"\" The very simplest reason is that the Constitution gives Congress the power","depth":8},{"id":89,"text":"to set terms of trade , not the executive branch , \"","depth":8},{"id":90,"text":"Todd Tucker , a fellow at the Roosevelt Institute , a liberal think tank","depth":9},{"id":91,"text":"based in New York ,","depth":9},{"id":92,"text":"told me .","depth":8},{"id":93,"text":"Congress","depth":9},{"id":94,"text":"- just as it needs to do for the USMCA -","depth":10},{"id":95,"text":"had to approve NAFTA .","depth":10},{"id":96,"text":"It did so through the 1993 NAFTA Implementation Act ,","depth":11},{"id":97,"text":"which is how Congress implements the provisions of NAFTA under US law .","depth":11},{"id":98,"text":"There ' s nothing in that law","depth":12},{"id":99,"text":"that says","depth":13},{"id":100,"text":"a president needs permission from Congress","depth":14},{"id":101,"text":"to terminate NAFTA ,","depth":14},{"id":102,"text":"Gary Clyde Hufbauer , a trade policy expert at the Peterson Institute of International Economics , told me .","depth":11},{"id":103,"text":"Which means Trump is probably free to do what he wants .","depth":10},{"id":104,"text":"But the president can ' t singlehandedly scrap that implementation law ,","depth":11},{"id":105,"text":"which means some of the provisions would remain in force .","depth":11},{"id":106,"text":"The end result ,","depth":10},{"id":107,"text":"Tucker said ,","depth":10},{"id":108,"text":"could be a kind of \" zombie NAFTA \"","depth":10},{"id":109,"text":"where the US isn ' t formally part of NAFTA ,","depth":11},{"id":110,"text":"but still trades","depth":12},{"id":111,"text":"much like it is .","depth":12},{"id":112,"text":"This is by no means a promising scenario ,","depth":8},{"id":113,"text":"and it wouldn ' t cushion the US from the economic uncertainty","depth":7},{"id":114,"text":"that would come from terminating a trillion-dollar trade agreement .","depth":7},{"id":115,"text":"Exactly how all of this would play out is untested and up for debate","depth":5},{"id":116,"text":"- which means","depth":6},{"id":117,"text":"that","depth":7},{"id":118,"text":"if Trump does attempt to withdraw from NAFTA ,","depth":8},{"id":119,"text":"he ' s almost definitely going to be challenged in court .","depth":8},{"id":120,"text":"Congress does have some remedies .","depth":5},{"id":121,"text":"It could potentially pass legislation","depth":9},{"id":122,"text":"to preempt actions by the administration","depth":9},{"id":123,"text":"and that prevents unilateral withdrawal from NAFTA .","depth":8},{"id":124,"text":"Or lawmakers could give themselves more power over trade","depth":9},{"id":125,"text":"and take some away from the president .","depth":9},{"id":126,"text":"The self-declared Tariff Man isn ' t going to be keen on giving up authority ,","depth":9},{"id":127,"text":"so these options of would likely require enough bipartisan support in Congress","depth":11},{"id":128,"text":"to withstand a presidential veto ,","depth":11},{"id":129,"text":"or be attached to must-pass legislation like , say , an upcoming spending bill .","depth":10},{"id":130,"text":"Trump hasn ' t formally sent a notice of withdrawal to Canada or Mexico yet .","depth":6},{"id":131,"text":"Larry Kudlow , the National Economic Council director , told reporters Monday","depth":7},{"id":132,"text":"that he thinks","depth":8},{"id":133,"text":"Trump \" is trying to light a fire under Congress , \"","depth":8},{"id":134,"text":"though he added","depth":7},{"id":135,"text":"he hadn ' t talked about it in much detail with the president .","depth":7},{"id":136,"text":"The lame-duck Congress","depth":10},{"id":137,"text":"- which will be spending most of its last days in office","depth":11},{"id":138,"text":"trying to avert a government shutdown -","depth":11},{"id":139,"text":"likely won ' t take up USMCA this session ,","depth":9},{"id":140,"text":"which means it falls to the new , divided Congress in 2019 .","depth":8},{"id":141,"text":"And Congress is apparently still undecided ,","depth":8},{"id":142,"text":"though Trump has said","depth":9},{"id":143,"text":"USMCA has gotten \" great reviews \"","depth":10},{"id":144,"text":"that are \" sooo much better than NAFTA. \"","depth":10},{"id":145,"text":"Both Republicans and Democrats have found something","depth":9},{"id":146,"text":"to dislike in USMCA .","depth":9},{"id":147,"text":"Great reviews on the USMCA","depth":9},{"id":148,"text":"- sooo much better than NAFTA !","depth":9},{"id":149,"text":"- Donald J. Trump","depth":9},{"id":150,"text":"( @ realDonaldTrump )","depth":9},{"id":151,"text":"November 30 , 2018","depth":8},{"id":152,"text":"Democrats largely support new labor provisions in the trade deal ,","depth":7},{"id":153,"text":"but have worried","depth":8},{"id":154,"text":"they won ' t go far enough","depth":10},{"id":155,"text":"to protect American workers ,","depth":10},{"id":156,"text":"and that labor and environmental standards lack sufficient enforcement mechanisms .","depth":9},{"id":157,"text":"\" Whatever they ' re calling it now ,","depth":11},{"id":158,"text":"it has some kind of gobbledygook name","depth":11},{"id":159,"text":"- the trade agreement","depth":11},{"id":160,"text":"formerly known as Prince ,","depth":12},{"id":161,"text":"no ,","depth":13},{"id":162,"text":"I mean ,","depth":14},{"id":163,"text":"formerly known as NAFTA -","depth":14},{"id":164,"text":"is a work in progress ,","depth":9},{"id":165,"text":"\" soon-to-be Speaker of the House Nancy Pelosi","depth":10},{"id":166,"text":"( D-CA )","depth":10},{"id":167,"text":"said last week ,","depth":9},{"id":168,"text":"adding","depth":8},{"id":169,"text":"that there aren ' t yet \" enough enforcement reassurances","depth":9},{"id":170,"text":"regarding provisions","depth":10},{"id":171,"text":"that relate to workers and to the environment . \"","depth":10},{"id":172,"text":"Republicans have also offered lukewarm reviews ,","depth":7},{"id":173,"text":"and have objected to some of the more restrictive provisions on the auto industry as well as the scaling back of a NAFTA provision","depth":8},{"id":174,"text":"that let corporations sue governments .","depth":8},{"id":175,"text":"There are also more local concerns ,","depth":7},{"id":176,"text":"including a complaint from Sen. Marco Rubio","depth":9},{"id":177,"text":"( R-FL )","depth":9},{"id":178,"text":"that the deal would hurt some Florida farmers .","depth":8},{"id":179,"text":"Republicans , however , are unlikely to buck the president on a signature trade accomplishment","depth":6},{"id":180,"text":"- especially since the USMCA alleviated fears among pro-free trade Republicans","depth":7},{"id":181,"text":"that Trump would abandon NAFTA altogether","depth":8},{"id":182,"text":"before a new deal could be negotiated .","depth":8},{"id":183,"text":"Sen. Chuck Grassley","depth":10},{"id":184,"text":"( R-IA ) ,","depth":10},{"id":185,"text":"who will chair the Senate Finance Committee","depth":10},{"id":186,"text":"that will usher the USMCA through the chamber in 2019 ,","depth":10},{"id":187,"text":"even gave a sort-of endorsement of the president ' s hardball strategy .","depth":8},{"id":188,"text":"\" That ' s a hard-nosed approach ,","depth":9},{"id":189,"text":"but sometimes the president has to use that","depth":10},{"id":190,"text":"if he wants to get things accomplished , \"","depth":10},{"id":191,"text":"Grassley said on a Monday radio show ,","depth":8},{"id":192,"text":"according to the Washington Post .","depth":6},{"id":193,"text":"Congress also is limited in how much it can tweak USMCA ,","depth":6},{"id":194,"text":"though there is some wiggle room .","depth":6},{"id":195,"text":"The USMCA has been signed ,","depth":8},{"id":196,"text":"but there are still a few more steps in the process","depth":8},{"id":197,"text":"before implementing legislation","depth":9},{"id":198,"text":"- which makes sure","depth":10},{"id":199,"text":"the USMCA matches up with and is adopted as US law -","depth":10},{"id":200,"text":"is introduced in the House and the Senate .","depth":8},{"id":201,"text":"Once it is ,","depth":8},{"id":202,"text":"the legislation will be \" fast-tracked , \"","depth":8},{"id":203,"text":"and lawmakers will have 90 days to approve it with an up or down vote ,","depth":8},{"id":204,"text":"meaning they can ' t make changes or add any amendments .","depth":8},{"id":205,"text":"Trade Representative Lighthizer has said","depth":8},{"id":206,"text":"there ' s no chance","depth":9},{"id":207,"text":"that the administration will reopen negotiations with Mexico and Canada .","depth":9},{"id":208,"text":"But the administration drafts the implementing legislation , typically with the consultation of Congress ,","depth":8},{"id":209,"text":"which means some bipartisan concerns could be addressed about the enforcement of some provisions ,","depth":10},{"id":210,"text":"which might ease its passage .","depth":10},{"id":211,"text":"( Lobbyists will certainly be weighing in as well . )","depth":9},{"id":212,"text":"Lighthizer said at the G20 meeting","depth":8},{"id":213,"text":"that he ' s open to addressing lawmakers ' issues in this process .","depth":8},{"id":214,"text":"He also told reporters last week","depth":9},{"id":215,"text":"he wants the USMCA to pass with strong bipartisan support .","depth":9},{"id":216,"text":"\" We ' ll get the support of a lot of Democrats , a very high number of Democrats , \"","depth":10},{"id":217,"text":"Lighthizer said .","depth":10},{"id":218,"text":"\" Absolutely , just no doubt about it . \"","depth":9},{"id":219,"text":"The problem , of course , is that bipartisan displeasure with USMCA doesn ' t mean consensus .","depth":9},{"id":220,"text":"If the administration accedes to any demands from one side ,","depth":10},{"id":221,"text":"it ' ll shore up opposition on the other side .","depth":10},{"id":222,"text":"Which might be the purpose of the NAFTA withdrawal threat :","depth":9},{"id":223,"text":"to prevent either Democrats or Republicans from asking too much ,","depth":10},{"id":224,"text":"and forcing them to accept the the USMCA in more or less its current form .","depth":10},{"id":225,"text":"But Trump might need to be wary of pushing it too far .","depth":7},{"id":226,"text":"In 2008 , House Democrats , then in the majority , accused President George W. Bush of trying to jam through a free trade agreement with Colombia ,","depth":11},{"id":227,"text":"saying","depth":12},{"id":228,"text":"the administration didn ' t do enough","depth":13},{"id":229,"text":"to address protections for US workers and human-rights abuses in Colombia .","depth":13},{"id":230,"text":"Then-Speaker Pelosi responded","depth":11},{"id":231,"text":"by blocking the agreement from \" fast track \" consideration altogether ,","depth":12},{"id":232,"text":"taking it off the accelerated timeline","depth":13},{"id":233,"text":"and putting the deal in jeopardy .","depth":13},{"id":234,"text":"( President Barack Obama ended up taking up a version of the Colombia agreement in his first term . )","depth":9},{"id":235,"text":"A Colombia trade deal isn ' t as massive or as critical as the USMCA ,","depth":11},{"id":236,"text":"and the US relationship with both Canada and Mexico is far more strategically and economically important .","depth":11},{"id":237,"text":"But Pelosi could threaten to un-fast-track the USMCA","depth":11},{"id":238,"text":"if the Trump administration pushes Democrats too far .","depth":11},{"id":239,"text":"\" It ' s completely discretionary -","depth":12},{"id":240,"text":"as long as she has the majority of support for it ,","depth":13},{"id":241,"text":"she could do it for whatever reason","depth":14},{"id":242,"text":"she wants , \"","depth":14},{"id":243,"text":"Tucker said .","depth":11},{"id":244,"text":"\" [ It ] doesn ' t have to be a certain legal reasoning ,","depth":11},{"id":245,"text":"it could just be , ' I don ' t like Trump today . ' \"","depth":11},{"id":246,"text":"There are political risks for Pelosi and the Democrats","depth":10},{"id":247,"text":"if they do this , though ,","depth":10},{"id":248,"text":"particularly if Trump terminates NAFTA","depth":10},{"id":249,"text":"and blames Democrats for the mess .","depth":10},{"id":250,"text":"But Trump unilateral move on NAFTA","depth":11},{"id":251,"text":"- which could have an immediate impact , particularly on financial markets -","depth":11},{"id":252,"text":"might unite both Republicans and Democrats","depth":11},{"id":253,"text":"who ' ve hesitated to stand up to Trump ' s bullying on trade so far .","depth":11},{"id":254,"text":"If Trump decides to kill NAFTA","depth":12},{"id":255,"text":"without another deal in place ,","depth":12},{"id":256,"text":"Tucker told me ,","depth":11},{"id":257,"text":"\" whatever political goodwill there is at the margins from Senate Republicans or House Democrats will go away pretty quickly . \"","depth":10}],"relations":[{"parent":515,"left":340,"right":514,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":340,"left":294,"right":339,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":294,"left":269,"right":293,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":269,"left":265,"right":268,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":265,"left":260,"right":264,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":260,"left":0,"right":259,"relation":"attribution","nuclearity":"SN"},{"parent":259,"left":1,"right":2,"relation":"organization","nuclearity":"SN"},{"parent":264,"left":261,"right":263,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":261,"left":3,"right":4,"relation":"context","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":263,"left":5,"right":262,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":262,"left":6,"right":7,"relation":"mode","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":268,"left":266,"right":267,"relation":"restatement","nuclearity":"NN"},{"parent":266,"left":8,"right":9,"relation":"attribution","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":267,"left":10,"right":11,"relation":"explanation","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":293,"left":277,"right":292,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":277,"left":271,"right":276,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":271,"left":12,"right":270,"relation":"organization","nuclearity":"SN"},{"parent":270,"left":13,"right":14,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":276,"left":272,"right":275,"relation":"joint","nuclearity":"NN"},{"parent":272,"left":15,"right":16,"relation":"joint","nuclearity":"NN"},{"parent":275,"left":274,"right":20,"relation":"joint","nuclearity":"NN"},{"parent":274,"left":17,"right":273,"relation":"attribution","nuclearity":"SN"},{"parent":273,"left":18,"right":19,"relation":"purpose","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":292,"left":289,"right":291,"relation":"restatement","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":289,"left":279,"right":288,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":279,"left":21,"right":278,"relation":"organization","nuclearity":"SN"},{"parent":278,"left":22,"right":23,"relation":"adversative","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":288,"left":284,"right":287,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":284,"left":281,"right":283,"relation":"joint","nuclearity":"NN"},{"parent":281,"left":24,"right":280,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":280,"left":25,"right":26,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":283,"left":27,"right":282,"relation":"adversative","nuclearity":"NN"},{"parent":282,"left":28,"right":29,"relation":"causal","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":287,"left":30,"right":286,"relation":"adversative","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":286,"left":31,"right":285,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":285,"left":32,"right":33,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":291,"left":290,"right":36,"relation":"joint","nuclearity":"NN"},{"parent":290,"left":34,"right":35,"relation":"joint","nuclearity":"NN"},{"parent":339,"left":314,"right":338,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":314,"left":295,"right":313,"relation":"organization","nuclearity":"SN"},{"parent":295,"left":37,"right":38,"relation":"adversative","nuclearity":"NN"},{"parent":313,"left":39,"right":312,"relation":"adversative","nuclearity":"NN"},{"parent":312,"left":299,"right":311,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":299,"left":40,"right":298,"relation":"joint","nuclearity":"NN"},{"parent":298,"left":41,"right":297,"relation":"attribution","nuclearity":"SN"},{"parent":297,"left":42,"right":296,"relation":"purpose","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":296,"left":43,"right":44,"relation":"joint","nuclearity":"NN"},{"parent":311,"left":306,"right":310,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":306,"left":303,"right":305,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":303,"left":302,"right":49,"relation":"condition","nuclearity":"SN"},{"parent":302,"left":45,"right":301,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":301,"left":46,"right":300,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":300,"left":47,"right":48,"relation":"purpose","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":305,"left":304,"right":52,"relation":"evaluation","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":304,"left":50,"right":51,"relation":"joint","nuclearity":"NN"},{"parent":310,"left":53,"right":309,"relation":"explanation","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":309,"left":54,"right":308,"relation":"attribution","nuclearity":"SN"},{"parent":308,"left":55,"right":307,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":307,"left":56,"right":57,"relation":"condition","nuclearity":"